@node introduction "What is MagicFile?!"

Introduction
------------
Everyone always seems to like file-taggers as seen on PC bbs's, and so
do I. When I started coding my CD-ROM-door for Xenolink I toyed with some
ideas and really liked the idea of making a file-tagger for Xenolink, 
not only for CD-ROM files,  but  also for the normal file catalogs. The
problem was that I really couldn't do it in C, as I had I just started 
learning it. So I waited  and I constructed my CD-ROM door piece by piece..
Very slowly it got better and I got better at coding C.  So a while after
Xenolink v1.90 arrived I released my CD-ROM door "MagicCD". I wanted to have
a try at the file catalog version.  And it went really well actually, I had
a working version in just one day!  Since then, it has improved a lot and
has become a full-featured file-tagger.

So here it is, the first and @{b}ONLY@{ub} file-tagger for Xenolink!

                               @{b}MagicFile@{ub}


(c)1994-1996 Manuel Groeneweg

@endnode
@node changes "Changes since MagicFile v1.6"
@{fg highlight}
@{i}WARNING: CHANGES HAVE BEEN MADE TO THE 'DOOR' TEMPLATE IN THE
MAGICFILE.CONFIG, IF YOU HAVE A REGISTERED VERSION OF MAGICFILE, PLEASE
CHANGE YOUR CONFIG ACCORDINGLY.@{ui}
@{fg text}

@{b}Changes to config keywords:@{ub}
 - Added an ACCESS argument to the DOOR keyword in the config.
 - Fixed the file buffering node-subdir bug.
 - Fixed config parsing bug, HELPFILE template wasn't parsed, MF always
   used a hardcoded path, now it doesn't anymore.


@{b}Other Changes:@{ub}
 - MagicFile now changes the 'action' field (for eg. Overseer) to
   'Browsing Files'.

@endnode
@node features "Features of MagicFile"

Features
--------
These are some of MagicFile's features:

 o Supports the following files:
     - Xenolinks standard file catalog
     - external configs (for CD-ROMS)
     - Aminet FILES.BBS
     - Gifs Galore 00_INDEX.TXT
     - Users private dir (from UserFileBox)

 o Optional buffering of CD-ROM files for systems with CD-ROM changers.

 o Supports external doors (with possible access restrictions) for eg.:
     - Downloading
     - Archive viewing
     - Long descriptions
     - File maintenance/editing
     - Anything you can write yourself

 o All text strings configurable
 o All keys configurable
 o All colors configurable
 o Online help through text file
 o Lots more, see for yourself!

@endnode
@node installation "Installing MagicFile"

Installation
------------

Just copy the whole MagicFile directory to 'DOORS:' and put an entry for
every file area in your menu(s). If you are @{"registered" link how_to} you can edit the
main @{"config" link magicfile.config} to your own needs.

Click @{"here" link arguments} for a list of command line arguments you can use with MagicFile.

@{b}Here is an example to have a quick first look at MagicFile:@{ub}

CMD = "1"
{
XenolinkDoor "Doors:MagicFile/MagicFile MODE=FILECAT AREA=1 XCBD=~20"
}

(AREA stands for the file area, if you don't have a file area 1 then you should
change 1 in a file area number which you do have)

You can use MagicFile in five different modes. Here are they explained
and an example is given:

 @{" FILECAT  " link arg_mode_filecat}
 @{" CD       " link arg_mode_cd}
 @{" PRIVATE  " link arg_mode_private}
@endnode
@node arguments "List of argument templates"

MagicFile uses ReadArgs() for it's command line parsing.

Here are the keywords:

@{"MODE"   link arguments_mode}
@{"CONFIG" link arguments_config}
@{"DATA"   link arguments_data}
@{"AREA"   link arguments_area}
@{"MINIMUMAGE" link arguments_minimumage}
@{"SCREENLENGTH" link arguments_screenlength}
@{"FREEDOWNLOAD" link arguments_freedownload}
@{"AREANAME" link arguments_areaname}
@{"XCBD" link arguments_xcbd}

@endnode
@node userfilebox "UserFileBox Quick Explaination.."

UserFileBox is a usefull addition to MagicFile. It enables sysops to give
their users a private file directory. This directory is in the 'Private/'
subdir in the users dir (where the .waitingmail etc. are kept).

The UserFileBox.rexx script supplied with MagicFile lets the user upload
a file privately to any other user on your bbs. The files can be listed
by no-one else then the user to whom the file got uploaded to. This must
be done in the PRIVATE mode in MagicFile.

Currently it has no size/access level restrictions or extended options but
when I find the time I'll try to do some more work on it.

Note: You'll need to have Junkmail in your path because the script calls it
to write a message informing the user to which the file got uploaded to.

Here's the menu entry for your menu source:

;
; Private Upload
;
CMD = "P"
{
  REXX "Doors:MagicFile/UserFileBox/userfilebox.rexx"
}


@endnode
@node how_to "How to register"

MagicFile is a shareware program, this  means  you can try it out for free
but if you like it you must pay a shareware fee to the author (that's me).

When you register you'll get

 - A keyfile which will unlock MagicFile and MagicEditor(*) and any future
   'Magic' doors/utilities I will make.

(*) MagicEditor is a sysop only GUI message editor using your favorite
    text editor (whichever you want).  Check your local support board.


Click on the country you live in:

@{" The Netherlands               " link a}
@{" Switzerland, Germany, Austria " link b}
@{" Other part of world           " link c}
@endnode
