@node config_waitloading "Template description"

@{i}Usage:@{ui} WAITLOADING <text>


@{i}Example:@{ui}

WAITLOADING "Please wait, loading..."


@{i}Notes:@{ui} This text will be printed on the screen when MagicFile loads
       the filedata.

@endnode
@node config_header "Template description"

@{i}Usage:@{ui} HEADER <text>


@{i}Example:@{ui}

HEADER " <up> Move Up - <down> Move Down  - <spc> Tag a File - <?> Commands - <q> Quit"


@{i}Notes:@{ui} This is the header which will be printed on top of the screen above
       the file-listings. You can show a few different commands that can be
       used in this line.

@endnode
@node config_areastring "Template description"

@{i}Usage:@{ui} AREASTRING <text>


@{i}Example:@{ui}

AREASTRING "File-area:"


@{i}Notes:@{ui} This string is printed in the header. The name of the current
       file area is printed after this string.

@endnode
@node config_noansimenuset "Template description"

@{i}Usage:@{ui} NOANSIMENUSET <text>


@{i}Example:@{ui}

NOANSIMENUSET "You need an ANSI menuset for MagicFile! <press key>"


@{i}Notes:@{ui} This will be printed when the user has an ascii menuset.

@endnode
@node config_noviewaccess "Template description"

@{i}Usage:@{ui} NOVIEWACCESS <text>


@{i}Example:@{ui}

NOVIEWACCESS "You have no access to this file area! <press key>"


@{i}Notes:@{ui} This will be printed when the user has no view access to the
       FILECAT area.

@endnode
@node config_nolistaccess "Template description"

@{i}Usage:@{ui} NOLISTACCESS <text>


@{i}Example:@{ui}

NOLISTACCESS "You have no access to this file area! <press key>"


@{i}Notes:@{ui} This will be printed when the user has no list access to the
       FILECAT area.

@endnode
@node config_tooyoung "Template description"

@{i}Usage:@{ui} TOOYOUNG <text>


@{i}Example:@{ui}

TOOYOUNG "You are too young for this file area! <press key>"


@{i}Notes:@{ui} This will be printed when the user is too young for this file area.

@endnode
@node config_nofilesinarea "Template description"

@{i}Usage:@{ui} NOFILESINAREA <text>


@{i}Example:@{ui}

NOFILESINAREA "There are no files in this file area! <press key>"

@{i}Notes:@{ui} This will be printed when there are no files in the file area.
@endnode
@node config_nofilesinprivate "Template description"

@{i}Usage:@{ui} NOFILESINPRIVATE <text>


@{i}Example:@{ui}

NOFILESINPRIVATE "There are no files in your private file area <press key>"

@{i}Notes:@{ui} This will be printed when there are no files in the users
       private file area.
@endnode
@node config_nodownloadaccess "Template description"

@{i}Usage:@{ui} NODOWNLOADACCESS <text>


@{i}Example:@{ui}

NODOWNLOADACCESS "You have no Download access in this file area! <press key>"


@{i}Notes:@{ui} This will be printed when the user has no download access in
       this file area.

@endnode
@node config_maxmarksexceeded "Template description"

@{i}Usage:@{ui} MAXMARKSEXCEEDED <text>


@{i}Example:@{ui}

MAXMARKSEXCEEDED "You may not mark any more files! <press key>"


@{i}Notes:@{ui} This will be printed when the user has exceeded the maximum
       number of files he may mark per time.

@endnode
@node config_dailybytesexceeded "Template description"

@{i}Usage:@{ui} DAILYBYTESEXCEEDED <text>


@{i}Example:@{ui}

DAILYBYTESEXCEEDED "File exceeds daily download limit! <press key>"


@{i}Notes:@{ui} This will be printed when the user has exceeded his daily bytes.


@endnode
@node config_fileratioexceeded "Template description"

@{i}Usage:@{ui} FILERATIOEXCEEDED <text>


@{i}Example:@{ui}

FILERATIOEXCEEDED "File exceeds file ratio! <press key>"


@{i}Notes:@{ui} This will be printed when the user had exceeded his file ratio.

@endnode
@node config_byteratioexceeded "Template description"

@{i}Usage:@{ui} BYTERATIOEXCEEDED <text>


@{i}Example:@{ui}

BYTERATIOEXCEEDED "File exceeds byte ratio! <press key>"


@{i}Notes:@{ui} This will be printed when the user has exceeded his byte ratio.

@endnode
@node config_beginningoflist "Template description"

@{i}Usage:@{ui} BEGINNINGOFLIST <text>


@{i}Example:@{ui}

BEGINNINGOFLIST "Beginning of list! <press key>"


@{i}Notes:@{ui} This will be printed when the user has reached the beginning of
       the file list while scrolling through the files.

@endnode
@node config_endoflist "Template description"

@{i}Usage:@{ui} ENDOFLIST <text>


@{i}Example:@{ui}

ENDOFLIST "End of list! <press key>"


@{i}Notes:@{ui} This will be printed when the user has reached the end of
       the file list while scrolling through the files.

@endnode
@node config_bufferingfilewait "Template description"

@{i}Usage:@{ui} BUFFERINGFILEWAIT <text>


@{i}Example:@{ui}

BUFFERINGFILEWAIT "Please wait, copying file to hd..."


@{i}Notes:@{ui} This will be printed while copying the file to the hd (only
       when the @{"BUFFERFILES" link config_bufferfiles} keyword is enabled.)

@endnode
@node config_errorbufferingfile "Template description"

@{i}Usage:@{ui} ERRORBUFFERINGFILE <text>


@{i}Example:@{ui}

ERRORBUFFERINGFILE "*** Error copying file, warn your sysop! *** <druk toets>"


@{i}Notes:@{ui} This will be printed if there is an error copying the file to the hd.
       (only when the @{"BUFFERFILES" link config_bufferfiles} keyword is enabled.)

@endnode
@node config_enterpattern "Template description"

@{i}Usage:@{ui} ENTERPATTERN <text>


@{i}Example:@{ui}

ENTERPATTERN "Enter search pattern: "


@{i}Notes:@{ui} The user will be prompted with this text when he wants to
       search for something.


@endnode
@node config_searching "Template description"

@{i}Usage:@{ui} SEARCHING <text>


@{i}Example:@{ui}

SEARCHING "Please wait, searching..."


@{i}Notes:@{ui} This text will be shown when MagicFile is searching for a 
       pattern the user entered.

@endnode
@node config_found "Template description"

@{i}Usage:@{ui} FOUND <text>


@{i}Example:@{ui}

FOUND "Found!"


@{i}Notes:@{ui} This text will be shown when MagicFile has found text matching
       the pattern the user entered.

@endnode
@node config_notfound "Template description"

@{i}Usage:@{ui} NOTFOUND <text>


@{i}Example:@{ui}

NOTFOUND "Nothing matches pattern! <press key>"


@{i}Notes:@{ui} This text will be shown when MagicFile couldn't find any
       matching text.

@endnode
@node config_colorheader "Template description"

@{i}Usage:@{ui} COLORHEADER <ansicolor>


@{i}Example:@{ui}

COLORHEADER "[44m"


@{i}Notes:@{ui} This is the ansi color for the header.

@endnode
@node config_colorname "Template description"

@{i}Usage:@{ui} COLORNAME <ansicolor>


@{i}Example:@{ui}

COLORNAME "[31m"


@{i}Notes:@{ui} This is the ansi color for the filename.

@endnode
@node config_colorsize "Template description"

@{i}Usage:@{ui} COLORSIZE <ansicolor>


@{i}Example:@{ui}

COLORSIZE "[36m"


@{i}Notes:@{ui} This is the ansi color for the filesize.

@endnode
@node config_coloraccesses "Template description"

@{i}Usage:@{ui} COLORACCESSES <ansicolor>


@{i}Example:@{ui}

COLORACCESSES "[35m"


@{i}Notes:@{ui} This is the ansi color for file accesses.

@endnode
@node config_colordesc "Template description"

@{i}Usage:@{ui} COLORDESC <ansistring>


@{i}Example:@{ui}

COLORDESC "[37m"


@{i}Notes:@{ui} This is the ansi color for the file description.

@endnode
@node config_showaccesses "Template description"

@{i}Usage:@{ui} SHOWACCESSES


@{i}Example:@{ui}

SHOWACCESSES


@{i}Notes:@{ui} This is a switch, if you put this template in your config the
       number of downloads will be printed in front of the description of the
       file (only in @{"FILECAT" link arg_mode_filecat} mode).

@endnode
@node config_bufferfiles "Template description"

@{i}Usage:@{ui} BUFFERFILES <path_to_copy_files_to>


@{i}Example:@{ui}

BUFFERFILES Xenolink:Temp/


@{i}Notes:@{ui} This is a switch, if you put this template in your config the
       files from your CD-ROM will be copied to the <node> subdir of 
       <path_to_copy_files_to> before they are downloaded by the user. This
       is often used for systems with CD-ROM-changers.

@endnode
@node config_maxmarks "Template description"

@{i}Usage:@{ui} MAXMARKS <number>


@{i}Example:@{ui}

MAXMARKS 25


@{i}Notes:@{ui} This template has the same function as the MaxMarkedFiles template
       in Xenolink general.config (there is no easy way to obtain that information
       for MagicFile afaik)

@endnode
@node config_helpfile "Template description"

@{i}Usage:@{ui} HELPFILE <file>


@{i}Example:@{ui}

HELPFILE Doors:MagicFile/Text/MagicFile.help


@{i}Notes:@{ui} The file given here should just contain an explanation of the
       several commands that can be used in MagicFile.

@endnode
@node config_door "Template description"

@{i}Usage:@{ui} DOOR <stack> <argstring> <key> <key> <accessrange>

stack:
    This is the required stack for the door

argstring:
    This is the argument string of the Xenolink door. Xenolink tilde codes
    are supported and ^F will be converted in the current file with path.

key:
    This can be any key as long as there are not two doors/actions with
    the same key, unless they have different accessrestrictions.

accessrange:
    This is the range of accesslevels which may enter this particular door.
    Valid ranges are eg. 5-25,100-255 or 5-255


@{i}Example:@{ui}

;This example will let anyone with an accesslevel between (and including)
;0 and 255 in the door.
;
DOOR 4096 "Doors:MagicFile/Bin/ViewArchive ^F ~20"  "v"  "V" 0-255

;
;This example will let only user with accesslevels 254 and 255
;in the door
DOOR 4096 "Doors:Utils/EditMarked ~20"  "e"  "E" 254-255

@{i}Notes:@{ui} Three small doors are included in the MagicFile archive,
       they are:
        Download - This door will send all the currently marked files to
                   the user. Needs ~20 as only argument.

        LongDescription - This door will get the full description of a
                          filecat file or the .readme file if one exists
                          (usually on Aminet cd's). Needs ^F as first and
                          ~20 as second argument.

        ViewArchive - This door will execute the XCONFIG:Arcview/.#? to view
                      the current archives description. Needs ^F as first and
                      ~20 as second argument.

@endnode
@node config_action "Template description"

@{i}Usage:@{ui} ACTION <action> <key> <key>

You should have an ACTION line for every type of action.

action:
    HELP     - brings up help screen
    QUIT     - quits MagicFile
    SEARCH   - start search function
    TAGFILE  - marks file for download
    FILEHOME - go to first file
    FILEEND  - go to last file
    FILEUP   - go one file up
    FILEDOWN - go one file down
    PAGEUP   - go one page up
    PAGEDOWN - go one page down

key:
    This can be any key you want to activate the action as long as there
    are not two actions/actions with the same key.


@{i}Example:@{ui}

ACTION HELP "?"  "?"


@{i}Notes:@{ui} 

@endnode
@node arguments_mode "Template description"

@{i}ReadArgs() template:@{ui} M=MODE/K/A

@{i}Usage:@{ui} MODE=<mode> @{i}or@{ui} M=<mode>

@{i}Notes:@{ui} This is the mode to start the door in.
       <mode> must be one of the following:

      @{" FILECAT  " link arg_mode_filecat} This mode loads the Xenolink file catalog data.
      @{" CD       " link arg_mode_cd} This mode loads Aminet cd FILES.BBS files, 00_INDEX.TXT
                  files from the Gifs Galore cd or the MagicFile custom
                  CD-ROM configs.
      @{" PRIVATE  " link arg_mode_private} This mode loads the current users private filedir.

@endnode
@node arguments_config "Template description"

@{i}ReadArgs() template:@{ui} C=CONFIG/K

@{i}Usage:@{ui} CONFIG=<config> @{i}or@{ui} C=<config>

@{i}Mode:@{ui} All modes.

@{i}Notes:@{ui} This is the general config file to load, if this keyword
       is left out,  MagicFile will take MagicFile.config  as a general
       config. This way you won't have to make a general config
       file for each area you've got.  Then  again you CAN make
       every area listing look different if you want to.  Strip
       'Doors:MagicFile/' from the path.


@endnode
@node arguments_data "Template description"

@{i}ReadArgs() template:@{ui} D=DATA/K

@{i}Usage:@{ui} DATA=<datafile> @{i}or@{ui} D=<datafile>

@{i}Mode:@{ui} CD

@{i}Notes:@{ui} This is either the FILES.BBS, the 00_INDEX.TXT or a custom
       CD-ROM data file. <datafile> is the FULL pathname!!

@endnode
@node arguments_area "Template description"

@{i}ReadArgs() template:@{ui} A=AREA/K

@{i}Usage:@{ui} AREA=<areanumber> @{i}or@{ui} A=<areanumber>

@{i}Mode:@{ui} FILECAT

@{i}Notes:@{ui} <areanumber> is the number of the file area to load,
       usually ~561, which is converted to the current file area.


@endnode
@node arguments_minimumage "Template description"

@{i}ReadArgs() template:@{ui} MA=MINIMUMAGE/K

@{i}Usage:@{ui} MINIMUMAGE=<age> @{i}or@{ui} MA=<age>

@{i}Mode:@{ui} CD

@{i}Notes:@{ui} <age> should be the minimum age the user must have to enter this
       CD-ROM area.

@endnode
@node arguments_screenlength "Template description"

@{i}ReadArgs() template:@{ui} SL=SCREENLENGTH/K

@{i}Usage:@{ui} SCREENLENGTH=<screenlength> @{i}or@{ui} SL=<screenlength>

@{i}Mode:@{ui} All modes.

@{i}Notes:@{ui} If you use this argument the screenlength of the door will
       be set to <screenlength>. Else MagicFile will adopt the users current
       screenlength.

@endnode
@node arguments_freedownload "Template description"

@{i}ReadArgs() template:@{ui} FD=FREEDOWNLOAD/S

@{i}Usage:@{ui} FREEDOWNLOAD @{i}or@{ui} FD

@{i}Mode:@{ui} CD

@{i}Notes:@{ui} This is a switch. If you use this all files in this area
       will be free download.

@endnode
@node arguments_areaname "Template description"

@{i}ReadArgs() template:@{ui} AN=AREANAME/K

@{i}Usage:@{ui} AREANAME=<areaname> @{i}or@{ui} AN=<areaname>

@{i}Mode:@{ui} CD

@{i}Notes:@{ui} If you start MagicFile in CD mode the area name in the header
       will show either the filename of the datafile, the comment of the
       data file or when AREANAME is set it will use <areaname> in the header.

@endnode
@node arguments_xcbd "Template description"

@{i}ReadArgs() template:@{ui} X=XCBD/K/A

@{i}Usage:@{ui} XCBD=<xcbd_pointer> @{i}or@{ui} X=<xcbd_pointer>

@{i}Mode:@{ui} All modes.

@{i}Notes:@{ui} Should always be ~20

@endnode
@node arg_mode_filecat "MODE=FILECAT"

This mode loads the normal Xenolink file catalog.
You also need to use the AREA argument for this mode.

Example for in your menu:

CMD = "1"
{
XenolinkDoor "Doors:MagicFile/MagicFile MODE=FILECAT AREA=1 XCBD=~20"
}

@endnode
@node arg_mode_cd "MODE=CD"

This mode loads @{b}FILES.BBS@{ub}, @{b}00_INDEX.TXT@{ub} or @{b}MagicFile CD-ROM filedata configs@{ub}.



@{b}- FILES.BBS -@{ub}

Example of a FILES.BBS entry for in your menu source:

CMD = "2"
{
XenolinkDoor "Doors:MagicFile/MagicFile MODE=CD DATA=CD0:AMINET/BIZ/DBASE/FILES.BBS AREANAME=BIZ/DBASE XCBD=~20"
}




@{b}- 00_INDEX.TXT -@{ub}

Example of a 00_INDEX.TXT entry for in your menu source:

CMD = "3"
{
XenolinkDoor "Doors:MagicFile/MagicFile MODE=CD DATA=CD0:GIFS/AVIATION/00_INDEX.TXT AREANAME=\"Gifs Galore: Aviation\" XCBD=~20"
}





@{b}- CD-ROM Filedata configs -@{ub}

The filedata configs are in the following format:

<filename>                (max. 30 chars)
<filesize>                (max.  8 chars)
<description>             (max. 60 chars)
<complete path of file>   (max. 50 chars)

example:

TESTFILE10.LHA
101220
Testfile v1.0 - Testfile for the example.
CD0:TESTDIR/FILES/
TESTFILE11.LHA
101221
Testfile v1.1 - Testfile for the example.
CD0:TESTDIR/FILES/
TESTFILE12.LHA
101222
Testfile v1.2 - Testfile for the example.
CD0:TESTDIR/FILES/
TESTFILE13.LHA
101223
Testfile v1.3 - Testfile for the example.
CD0:TESTDIR/FILES/


The comment of the data file will be used as the area-name in MagicFile's
header.

I have lots of 'ready-to-go' configs for all kinds of cd's on my bbs.
You can freq or just download them from my @{"bbs" link bbs}.
You can also get them from http://www.xs4all.nl/~voyage/

Click @{"here" link list} for the list.

Example for in your menu:

CMD = "4"
{
XenolinkDoor "Doors:MagicFile/MagicFile MODE=CD DATA=Doors:MagicFile/Porno2/sm.cfg MINIMUMAGE=21 XCBD=~20"
}

@endnode
@node arg_mode_private "MODE=PRIVATE"

This mode loads the files from 'Xenolink:Users/<user>/Private/'

Click @{"here" link userfilebox} for more info on this.

Example for in your menu:

CMD = "5"
{
XenolinkDoor "Doors:MagicFile/MagicFile MODE=PRIVATE FREEDOWNLOAD XCBD=~20"
}

@endnode
@node future "This is the Future!"

 - Sorting of the file listings (ALPHA/RALPHA/CHRONO/RCHRONO/SIZE etc..)
 - Newfiles scan mode
 - Changearea option
 - Searching on multiple cd's (even if not online)

Suggestions are more than welcome!

@endnode
